CatDescriptText: Sign reads "Pull down first lever to vote straight democratic, the best government at the lowest possible cost; Judge of the Supreme Court Michael J. Eagen; Judge of the Superior Court Harry M. Montgomery; Judges of the Court of Common Pleas - Vote for 3: Henry X. O'Brien, J. Frank McKenna, Jr., Robert Van Der Voort; Judge of the County Court Nathaniel K. Beck; County Commissioner - Vote for 2: John E. McGrady, William D. McClelland; County Controller James W. Knox; District Attorney Edward C. Boyle; County Treasurer Norman Carpenter; Register of Wills Rita Wilson Kane; Prothonotary David B. Roberts; Recorder of Deeds John J. Exler; Mayor Joseph M. Barr; City Controller Edward R. Frey; Members of the Council - vote for 4: Charles D. McCarthy, Irma M. D'Ascenzo, John F. Counahan, Paul F. Jones"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women and men gathered around sign reading "Pull down first lever to vote straight democratic...", posed in front of brick building
